==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Solifidian
<hw>Sol`i*fid"i*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>solus</ets> alone + <ets>fides</ets> faith.]</ety>
<fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>One who maintains that faith alone, without
works, is sufficient for justification; -- opposed to
<contr>nullifidian</contr>.</def> <rj><au>Hammond.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solifidian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Solifidian
<hw>Sol`i*fid"i*an</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Holding the tenets of
Solifidians; of or pertaining to the solifidians.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solifidianism</ent>⟦br⟧
